  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan Civilian Protection Activity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Afghan government and security forces have increased capacity to protect civilians; 2. Afghan NGOs through CIVIC-mentored CPWGs have increased capacity to engage with security forces and local government; 3. Councils of community elders (shuras) are provided with tools and knowledge about civilian protection to engage with security forces and armed opposition groups; 4. Resolute Support (NATO) contributes to the effort to reduce civilian harm; 5. The government of Afghanistan has improved understanding of the policies that contribute to stability in southern Afghanistan and considers their applicability to the northeast.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CIVIC is advising the Government of Afghanistan on a national plan of action for implementing newly-adopted civilian protection policies; mentoring nascent Afghan civil society organizations; organizing, training, and guiding traditional community elders to engage armed actors for community protection; and ensuring that NATO&#x2019;s Resolute Support (RS) mission prioritizes civilian protection as they increase military operations in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
